# Yii2 Advanced — File Placement

## Application tiers

| Tier | Path | Purpose |
|------|------|---------|
| Backend | `backend/` | Admin panel (AdminLTE 3) |
| Frontend | `frontend/` | Public web app |
| API | `api/` | REST API (v1 module) |
| Console | `console/` | CLI commands & cron jobs |
| Common | `common/` | Shared across all tiers |

## Where PHP files go

| Type | Location |
|------|----------|
| Shared models | `common/models/` |
| Backend controllers | `backend/controllers/` |
| Backend views | `backend/views/{controller-id}/` |
| Backend widgets | `backend/widgets/` |
| Frontend controllers | `frontend/controllers/` |
| Frontend views | `frontend/views/{controller-id}/` |
| Console commands | `console/controllers/` |
| Migrations | `console/migrations/` |
| API controllers | `api/modules/v1/controllers/` |
| Mail templates | `common/mail/` |
| Test seeders | `database/seeds/` |
| Config files | `{app}/config/` |

## NEVER place PHP classes in the project root
